---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Debt in context
description: UK debt and annual debt interest set next to familiar areas of annual public spending.
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import caveatBox, dataFreshnessBadge %}

{% set netDebt = dashboard.metrics | findBy("id", "net-debt") %}
{% set interest = dashboard.metrics | findBy("id", "debt-interest") %}

<div class="page-intro prose">
  <h1>Debt in context</h1>
  <p class="lede">Large sums mean more when set beside things we recognise. Here is the debt, and the yearly interest on it, next to annual spending areas.</p>
</div>

<section aria-labelledby="interest-context">
  <h2 id="interest-context">Annual debt interest ({{ interest.value | poundsShort }}) compared with…</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="Debt interest compared with spending areas">
    <table class="data-table">
      <caption>Annual debt interest as a share of each spending area</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Spending area</th><th scope="col" class="num">Annual amount</th><th scope="col" class="num">Interest is about</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for area in spendingComparisons.areas %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">{{ area.name }}</th>
          <td class="num">£{{ area.value | number }} bn</td>
          <td class="num">{{ (interest.value / area.value * 100) | round(0) }}% of it</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="debt-context">
  <h2 id="debt-context">Total debt ({{ netDebt.value | poundsShort }}) compared with…</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="Total debt compared with spending areas">
    <table class="data-table">
      <caption>Total net debt as a multiple of each annual spending area</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Spending area</th><th scope="col" class="num">Annual amount</th><th scope="col" class="num">Debt is about</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for area in spendingComparisons.areas %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">{{ area.name }}</th>
          <td class="num">£{{ area.value | number }} bn</td>
          <td class="num">{{ (netDebt.value / area.value) | round(1) }}× a year</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<p class="source-note">
  Spending figures: HM Treasury and related departmental sources, fiscal year {{ spendingComparisons.fiscalYear }}.
  Retrieved {{ spendingComparisons.areas[0].retrieved_date | readableDate }}.
  {{ dataFreshnessBadge("estimated", "") }}
</p>

{{ caveatBox("Based on latest available annual spending figures. These comparisons show scale only. They do not imply that any of these budgets could be redirected to pay down debt, or that debt could be swapped for spending. The state pension is also included within total welfare and social protection.", "How to read these comparisons") }}
